Speaker 1: Thanks, Juan Villagra, Quinn speaking.

Speaker 2: How can I help you?

Speaker 1: Yes, I wanted to call and just confirm

Speaker 2: that my prescription's been canceled.

Speaker 1: I keep getting shipments and charges,

Speaker 2: and I sought a cancellation notice.

Speaker 1: The last one was on January 2nd.

Speaker 2: Okay, let's pull up your account one moment.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And how exactly did you send a cancellation notice?

Speaker 1: I don't see any phone calls or anything.

Speaker 2: Well, there was an email sent,

Speaker 1: and I got a reply back on January 2nd.

Speaker 2: And what did that reply back say?

Speaker 1: Reply back said,

Speaker 2: it's an important update regarding my prescription.

Speaker 1: Went on to say something about due to overwhelming demand

Speaker 2: to proceed with canceling your prescription,

Speaker 1: please call our toll-free number

Speaker 2: and speak directly with a live agent.

Speaker 1: I tried calling before with an internal wait,

Speaker 2: but I was just shooting back another confirmation

Speaker 1: that I asked for it to be canceled,

Speaker 2: and it hasn't canceled yet.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you have to follow those instructions

Speaker 2: to call us, as the email said.

Speaker 1: Well, but I said in the email, cancel my prescription,

Speaker 2: and also that there's a charge on my card today.

Speaker 1: Correct.

Speaker 2: It's canceled on January 2nd.

Speaker 1: But you didn't cancel on January 2nd,

Speaker 2: so you just sent the email,

Speaker 1: and then you didn't follow the instructions

Speaker 2: to the reply to that email.

Speaker 1: Well, did the shipment go out?

Speaker 2: Yeah, yeah, the order went out,

Speaker 1: but I'm referring to you canceling in January.

Speaker 2: You did not cancel in January.

Speaker 1: You sent an email about canceling.

Speaker 2: We sent you a reply to call us, so we can do it for you.

Speaker 1: Don't start this shit with me.

Speaker 2: Do not start this with me.

Speaker 1: I called back, I called back,

Speaker 2: and I told y'all that I was canceling the prescription.

Speaker 1: I explicitly explained that in the email.

Speaker 2: I called back, I was on eternal hold,

Speaker 1: and now here we are getting another charge.

Speaker 2: What is eternal hold?

Speaker 1: I'm not sure what that means.

Speaker 2: You've been putting me on hold forever,

Speaker 1: so I don't have time to sit around

Speaker 2: and wait for someone to talk to me.

Speaker 1: I send it in an email, cancel it, and I'm done.

Speaker 2: Email is not valid, sir.

Speaker 1: That's why we-

Speaker 2: Well, I'm telling you now, cancel it.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'm just-

Speaker 2: I'm telling you right now.

Speaker 1: I understand, but you did not cancel in January.

Speaker 2: That's all I'm trying to get to clarity.

Speaker 1: Well, that's a bunch of crock, that's a crock.

Speaker 2: It's not, sir.

Speaker 1: We clearly sent you a reply on how to cancel,

Speaker 2: and you did not do it.

Speaker 1: So, how is that?

Speaker 2: I mean, we tried to help you.

Speaker 1: We can't, if we give you information,

Speaker 2: you don't follow instructions,

Speaker 1: then I don't understand how it's a crock.

Speaker 2: Well, it is.

Speaker 1: Very clear, it's very clear.

Speaker 2: It's very clear what I did,

Speaker 1: and I was put on hold for 15 minutes,

Speaker 2: and everybody answered the call.

Speaker 1: We're busy, 15 minutes is a long time.

Speaker 2: Don't start with this.

Speaker 1: Cancel it today.

Speaker 2: I'm refusing charges,

Speaker 1: and I don't want to hear from y'all again.

Speaker 2: You understand?

Speaker 1: Thank you.
